Here's some basic information: in addition to https://wallet.bittensor.com/ (from the Opentensor team), there are several other options. First, there's https://tensorwallet.ca/, by our very own Vune. In addition, most Polkadot ecosystem wallets work with TAO, including the powerful but complex polkadot.js (https://polkadot.js.org/), Talisman (https://www.talisman.xyz/), and Nova Wallet (https://novawallet.io/). And for if you are very security-oriented, there's the air-gapped Polkadot Vault (https://signer.parity.io/#about), which you can run on an old Android phone or iPhone. 

Since your tokens exist on-chain and wallets are just interfaces to interact with them, feel free to try a few and see what you like best!

At this particular time, there isn't an Etherscan-style explorer where you can plug in a wallet address and get a full accounting of that wallet's holdings and transaction history.  Bittensor does not have a presence on Polkascan yet, but my understanding is that it's in the works.  I just won't be able to tell you when it'll be available, though I know it'll be announced in the #📣・announcements channel once it's live.

Right now, the only way to find out the balance of your wallet is to open up your wallet in one of the supported wallets and look.

As we bid farewell to Subnet 3, due to recent incentive changes, we can take a moment to reminisce.

Subnet 3 was a proving ground for raw LLM capability by measuring next token prediction (NTP) accuracy.
It featured many innovations like scaling law parameter estimates, batch-wise Shapley scoring, logit excess anomaly detection/punishment, and much more.
Ran like a champ for +6 months without any significant changes needed, and for many more months before that, being in service for about a year.

Here's the familiar neuron stats table from a Subnet 3 validator log.

Subnet 3 is still purring along, but miners will start to drop due to no incentive, but this is planned obsolescence as we now prioritize sequence generation instead of NTP.

Even though we did not recently do any in-depth analytics of Subnet 3, regular spot-checks did not reveal any exploits or anomalies via the logit excess and loss ranges observed.

Here's a Subnet 3 log table with some of the next-token prediction tasks in a batch request.

howdy folks, i've gotten some reports from community members that their validator vtrust is dropping and they're seeing a lot of `blacklist` messages. we believe this may be due to some of the miners left from the previous group that tried to take over subnet 1. It seems they are blacklisting the smaller validators and trying to exclusively work with the big validators. This might be an attempt to reduce their own network traffic, we are looking into the reasoning. 

**The good news**
- This group's known hotkeys have reduced to the double digits as of posting this message, and they continue to drop. This is due to the punishing nature of the new validation mechanism, if it sees a response it deems to be cached or not coming from a true model, it rewards them 0 (i.e. not fractions or less reward).  Hence even focusing on the big validators won't help. 
- As a result, this behavior shouldn't last long until the network does a full turn over and we have more 'trustworthy' miners. 

**The bad news**
- In the meantime, some validators with stake less than 20k tao might get deregistered if their vtrust continues to fall. My recommendation is to stay and do not remove your validator as it only helps. We are investigating this.
